page.title: 11ECOLOGY .
page.content: THE AREA HAS A MILD CLIMATE,RAINFALL IS EXTREMELY HEAVY ALL YEAR ROUND. {POLLUTION}THERE IS NO LOCAL POLLUTION. LICHEN IS ABUNDANT ON TREES AND WALLS. {ANIMALS&BIRDS }THERE ARE A NUMBER OF RARE BIRDS AND ANIMALS.THESE INCLUDE GOLDEN EAGLE,PEREGRINE FALCON,SEA EAGLE,PEACOCKS,WILDCAT,STOAT,PINE MARTEN AND OTTER. {FISH }FISH IN ABUNDANCE INCLUDE SALMON,SEA,BROWN&RAINBOW TROUT,CHAR AND EELS. {TREES}THE MOST COMMON TREES ARE ASH,OAK,BIRCH,ALDER,PINE,ROWAN,HOLLY, BEECH AND RHODODENDRON. {CONSERVATION }DUE TO THE VERY LIMITED USE OF THE LAND AS YET,CONSERVATION OF EXISTING FEATURES IS NOT A PROBLEM.AS DEVELOPEMENT IS PLANNED SHORTLY THIS MAY YET ARISE.
